  {
    "client_msg_id": "49c0bac4-6083-4003-b826-39bc250ccc39",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Minute 19: :+1::+1:\nThis presentation is mainly about their immediate-mode GUI. It was interesting to see and think about how problems are solved in the IMGUI context - I'm not sure if the presentation mentioned explicitly how you keep track of the keyboard focus, current scroll-bar position in a list, or selection info in a textbox, but I guess it's \"by ID\" (you could include this kind of info in your data model, but that could be inconvenient). But then, how do you solve the problem of giving every control an ID that is both unique and stable?",
    "user": "UD6EXQVM0",
    "ts": "1584555156.397000",
